# Deben, Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Deben () is a rural locality (an ulus) in Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 158 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Deben is located 81&nbsp;km south of Gusinoozyorsk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nur-Tukhum is the nearest rural locality.
